result.execSummary:
The defendant Latia D Abbott was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[ml] Cases 21CF328, 21CF329, and 22CF1 called at 1:31PM
Defendant Latia D Abbott in court with attorney William Ginsberg. ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.

Initial appearance in 22CF1:
The Defendant verifies that the date of birth and address listed on the Criminal Complaint are correct. 
Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived, the charges and maximum penalties are recited.

Ms. Abbott waives her right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds her over for Trial.

Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived
--the charges and maximum penalties are recited

---------------------------------------------

The Court proceeds with sentencing in all the above files:

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " GUILTY " entered as to Counts #1 and #5 in file 21CF328, and Count #2 in file 22CF1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #2, #3, and #4 in file 21CF328, Counts #1 and #2 in file 21CF329, and Counts #1, #3, and #4 in file 22CF1.
Counts #1 and #5 in file 21CF328, and Count #2 in file 22CF1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, with conditions:
--Comply with ALL conditions of Jefferson County Drug Treatment Court
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment per Agent
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling per Agent
--random drug/alcohol testing per agent
--attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program per Agent
--absolute sobriety (no possession or consumption of alcohol, no possession or consumption of controlled substances without a valid prescription, take any and all prescriptions only as prescribed by treating physician)
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes or as deemed appropriate per agent
--if permitted to travel out of state: no possession or use of marijuana (THC) in states where it is legal.  No legal CBD products or other legal cannabis derivatives without express written permission of the Agent
--DNA provision sample and surcharge

The Court does not order any Driver License suspension or revocation.
The Court finds that the Defendant is not eligible for expungement due to her age and for reasons stated on the record.

Separate from the conditions of Probation, the Court orders payment of costs, fees and surcharges through the Clerk of Courts Office. [Clerk calculates this total to be: $1,804.00; this includes Drug Testing fees in the amount of $50.00 in file 21CF329, $200.00 in file 21CF328, and $75.00 in file 22CF1] The Court grants the Defendant sixty days to either pay the amount in full or to establish a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office.  Non-payment will result in 38 days in Jail with Huber privileges, consecutive (15 days on Count #1 in file 21CF328, 8 days on Count #5 in file 21CF328, and 15 days on Count #2 in file 22CF1).

Credit for time already served:
22CF1: 1 day on Count #2
21CF328: 1 day on Count #2

Judgment of Conviction to indicate: "DRUG TREATMENT COURT PARTICIPANT"  

Felony firearm/civil rights warning given
